{"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/getSystemDataDirs()"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"getSystemDataDirs","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">?>!","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On UNIX platforms this is determined using the mechanisms described"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"http:\/\/www.freedesktop.org\/Standards\/basedir-spec","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"In this case the list of directories retrieved will be ","type":"text"},{"code":"XDG_DATA_DIRS","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On Windows it follows XDG Base Directory Specification if ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"XDG_DATA_DIRS"},{"text":" is defined.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"XDG_DATA_DIRS","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is undefined,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the first elements in the list are the Application Data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and Documents folders for All Users. (These can be determined only","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on Windows 2000 or later and are not present in the list on other","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Windows versions.) See documentation for FOLDERID_ProgramData and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"FOLDERID_PublicDocuments.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Then follows the “share” subfolder in the installation folder for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the package containing the DLL that calls this function, if it can"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be determined.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Finally the list contains the “share” subfolder in the installation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"folder for GLib, and in the installation folder for the package the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"application’s .exe file belongs to.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The installation folders above are determined by looking up the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"folder where the module (DLL or EXE) in question is located. If the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"folder’s name is “bin”, its parent is used, otherwise the folder","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"itself."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that on Windows the returned list can vary depending on where","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this function is called.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The return value is cached and modifying it at runtime is not supported, as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it’s not thread-safe to modify environment variables at runtime.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib17getSystemDataDirsSPySPys4Int8VGSgGSgyF","symbolKind":"func","title":"getSystemDataDirs()","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"getSystemDataDirs","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">?>!","kind":"text"}],"roleHeading":"Function"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns an ordered list of base directories in which to access"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"system-wide application data."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/getsystemdatadirs()"]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/getSystemDataDirs()":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/getSystemDataDirs()","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/getsystemdatadirs()","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns an ordered list of base directories in which to access"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"system-wide application data.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"getSystemDataDirs","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">?>!"}],"title":"getSystemDataDirs()","type":"topic"},"http://www.freedesktop.org/Standards/basedir-spec":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"XDG Base Directory Specification"}],"title":"XDG Base Directory Specification","identifier":"http:\/\/www.freedesktop.org\/Standards\/basedir-spec","url":"http: